article.headline: Quinnipiac 88, Sacred Heart 83 (OT)
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. (AP) -- Rob Monroe scored 36 of his game-high 40 points after the first half break to lead Quinnipiac to an 88-83 overtime win over Sacred Heart Thursday in Northeast Conference play. Monroe, who missed his first six 3-point attempts, finished 5-of-14 from beyond the arc, including two in overtime. He also had six assists. C.J. Vick had 14 points for the Bobcats (8-11, 4-6 NEC), who snapped a five-game losing streak. Da-Shawn Dwight added a career-high 12 points, six assists and eight rebounds. Joey Henley led Sacred Heart (3-16, 2-8) with 19 points and 10 rebounds. His finger roll with 55 seconds left sent the game into overtime tied at 71-71. Sacred Heart trailed by seven with 3:26 left before scoring the final seven points of regulation. Eugene Pettway had 16 points, Mike Parker 14 points Ryon Howard 10 for Sacred Heart.
